complishment at SFIS came this
year. I made it through high school,
and now I will face the real world.
I would like to say thanks to all the
teachers for passing their knowl
edge on to me. To my friends, Keela,
Benina, Toy, Marcy, and Erykah,
thanks for making my high school
years exciting and most memo
rable. To my family, thanks for your
encouragement; it worked. I actu
ally made it! And to my lovely
daughter, Debriana, thank you for
giving me the strength to face each
day; knowing that you would be
waiting for me when I got home,
has made all the difference. I love
you always, sweetheart. To the se
nior class, good luck in all you do.
Remember, the class of 2000 is da
bomb! Favorite quote: All life is an
experiment. The more experiments
you make the better. Ralph Waldo
Emerson
